==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philippic
<hw>Phi*lip"pic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Philippiko`s</ets> belonging to Philip, Philippic, Gr.
<grk>filippikos</grk>, fr. <grk>Fi`lippos</grk> Philip,
<grk>fi`lippos</grk> fond of horses: cf. F.
<ets>philippique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any one of the series of
famous orations of Demosthenes, the Grecian orator, denouncing Philip,
king of Macedon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: Any discourse or declamation abounding in
acrimonious invective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philippine</ent>⟦br⟧
